->  LeetCode 584 – Find Customer Referee
Pattern

Filtering + NULL Handling

Trick

Use IS NULL because NULL != 2 does not evaluate to TRUE.

Mistakes
Used only != 2
Forgot OR referee_id IS NULL
Complexity

Time: O(n)

Query
SELECT name
FROM Customer
WHERE referee_id != 2
   OR referee_id IS NULL;


->  LeetCode 595 – Big Countries
Pattern

Filtering (WHERE)

Trick

The problem requires OR, not AND.

Mistakes
Used AND
Compared numbers as strings ('3000000')
Complexity

Time: O(n)

Query
SELECT name, population, area
FROM World
WHERE area >= 3000000
   OR population >= 25000000;


-> LeetCode 1148 – Article Views I
Pattern

Filtering + DISTINCT

Trick

Remove duplicate authors using DISTINCT.

Mistakes
Forgot DISTINCT
Forgot alias AS id
Forgot ORDER BY
Complexity

Time: O(n)

Query
SELECT DISTINCT author_id AS id
FROM Views
WHERE author_id = viewer_id
ORDER BY id;


-> LeetCode 1683 – Invalid Tweets
Pattern

String Functions

Trick

Use CHAR_LENGTH() instead of .length.

Mistakes
Wrote content.length
Confused Java syntax with SQL
Complexity

Time: O(n)

Query
SELECT tweet_id
FROM Tweets
WHERE CHAR_LENGTH(content) > 15;


-> LeetCode 1378 – Replace Employee ID With The Unique Identifier
Pattern

LEFT JOIN

Trick

Keep all employees even if they don't have a unique ID.

Mistakes
Used INNER JOIN
Didn't understand table aliases (e, eu)
Complexity

Time: O(n)

Query
SELECT eu.unique_id,
       e.name
FROM Employees e
LEFT JOIN EmployeeUNI eu
ON e.id = eu.id;


-> LeetCode 1581 – Customer Who Visited but Did Not Make Any Transactions
Pattern

LEFT JOIN + GROUP BY

Trick

Find rows with no match using IS NULL.

Mistakes
Used HAVING instead of WHERE
Compared customer_id instead of visit_id
Didn't group by customer_id
Complexity

Time: O(n)

Query
SELECT v.customer_id,
       COUNT(*) AS count_no_trans
FROM Visits v
LEFT JOIN Transactions t
ON v.visit_id = t.visit_id
WHERE t.visit_id IS NULL
GROUP BY v.customer_id;


